"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-leon-marchand-pulled-off-the-unthinkable-winning-two-golds-two-hours-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 It was 11:32 p.m., the end of a day unlike any Olympic swimming has ever seen.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 88, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The man who had just performed the greatest single-session feat in the history of his sport was standing at an elevator, waiting for it to open and take him down and away from a venue he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d transformed into a roaring SEC football stadium.\\u00c2  L\\u00c3\\u00a9on Marchand, an unremarkable physical specimen dressed in his white French podium sweats, was beginning the refueling process by munching on a snack and sipping on a bottle of water.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 307, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeastern_Conference\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5188645374697106e-17, \"text\": \"SEC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeastern_Conference\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeastern_Conference\"}, {\"begin\": 337, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone had painted a thin streak of France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s flag colors\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094red, white and blue\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094on his left cheek.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the elevator taking its sweet time, a staffer at La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena seized the opportunity to ask Marchand for a selfie, which he granted with a smile.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For a man who had just turned the Olympics into his own five-ring revival, Marchand was perfectly chill.\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Very happy, and assuredly very tired, but also entirely composed.\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone else was properly gobsmacked by Le Roi L\\u00c3\\u00a9on.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old from Toulouse had just completed the L\\u00c3\\u00a9on Double, something mere mortal wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t dare attempt, much less conquer.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Toulousain\", \"score\": 0.9950559580058935, \"rank\": 0.0049686068081441674, \"text\": \"Toulouse\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Toulousain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Toulousain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won the 200-meter butterfly at 8:42 p.m., then turned around and won the 200 breaststroke at 10:36 p.m., an accomplishment of Promethean audacity.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prometheus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.504989857388957e-22, \"text\": \"Promethean\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prometheus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prometheus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He electrified his home country, astounded his sport and even surprised himself.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI knew it was possible for me to just finish those races,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said, then laughed.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMaybe not win them.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  He won them.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were gold medals No.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2 and 3 for Marchand of these Olympics, with another one likely on Friday in the 200 individual medley, if his body holds up after this incredible effort.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this was so much more than that.\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nobody had won two individual events in the same Olympic session in nearly 50 years, since Kornelia Ender in 1976.\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kornelia_Ender\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kornelia Ender\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kornelia_Ender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kornelia_Ender\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was from East Germany at the height of its PED doping prowess, so let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just say those gold medals have come under some suspicion.\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7148099664347134e-16, \"text\": \"East Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4609102289010514e-24, \"text\": \"PED\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ender won the 200 freestyle and 100 butterfly that day in Montreal; winning a pair of 200s ups the degree of difficulty even more.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2553073186473822e-11, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Lochte won medals in two different events on the same day in both 2012 and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009908, but he didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t win two golds.\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Lochte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A male Olympic swimmer hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t won two individual golds on the same day in more than a century.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is more than all that, too.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand set Olympic records winning both races, in addition to his Olympic record in the 400 individual medley Sunday.\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also was the first to conquer theSlow Pool energy drain, a mysterious malady in a shallow venue that may have contributed to the first nine leaders of finals races of 200 meters or shorter failing to hold on in the final 50 meters.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there are still more layers to this feat.\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In both races, Marchand dethroned the reigning Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And he did it in opposite ways.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He led Australian Zac Stubblety-Cook the entire 200 meters in the breaststroke, and heroared back spectacularlyin the final 50 to defeat Hungarian Krist\\u00c3\\u00b3f Mil\\u00c3\\u00a1k in the butterfly.\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 3033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2860, \"end\": 2870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9948708263431492, \"rank\": 0.005155425400589069, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2990, \"end\": 2999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999864915574282, \"rank\": 1.3485809319203662e-05, \"text\": \"Hungarian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which gets to the final element that made this an unforgettable night in swimming lore.\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Inspired by their local hero, the crowd of about 17,000 produced a night of non-stop noise that may be unmatched in swimming annals.\", \"from\": 3123, \"to\": 3255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(If anything comes close, it was Sydney in 2000 when Ian Thorpe was in superstar mode.)\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3289, \"end\": 3295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9877862646863913, \"rank\": 0.012364754924814125, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 3309, \"end\": 3319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ian Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt felt like a rugby game,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Stubblety-Cook.\", \"from\": 3344, \"to\": 3397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t hear.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The crowd was deafening before, during and after the Marchand triumphs.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it reached peak pandemonium in the final 50 meters of the butterfly race, as Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094nearly a full second behind\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094exploded off the final turn with a powerful series of underwater kicks to turn the improbable into reality.\", \"from\": 3496, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rally was happening, it was reminiscent of the noise that accompanied Auburn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kick Six at Jordan-Hare Stadium in the 2013 Iron Bowl.\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not quite that loud\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094that had about 70,000 more fans than this competition\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094but in terms of disbelief turning into unconfined celebration.\", \"from\": 3881, \"to\": 4021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both comebacks had an Oh My God This Is Really Going To Happen shock value to them.\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe two fly was actually crazy on the last 50,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Marchand said.\", \"from\": 4107, \"to\": 4174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI could hear underwater that the pool was going crazy.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  When that race was over, Marchand indulged in a hearty celebration but didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t go overboard, knowing what the back half of the double would entail.\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He left the pool deck and re-emerged less than an hour later for the medal ceremony, wearing those white sweats for the first time in the evening.\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 9:38 p.m. the French national anthem played, and Marchand sang along, and then he bid his fellow medalists a quick au revoir while they toured the pool deck and had their pictures taken.\", \"from\": 4533, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4550, \"end\": 4572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\"}, {\"begin\": 4585, \"end\": 4593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand resumed his prep for the breaststroke at that point, heading back to the warmup pool and then to the ready room to line up for introductions.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the pool deck, American legend Katie Ledecky exited the stage at 10:29 p.m. afterreceiving her eighth career gold medal.\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4893, \"end\": 4901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999923994807963, \"rank\": 7.383610042917564e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4909, \"end\": 4922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A minute later, the chants of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cL\\u00c3\\u00a9-on!\", \"from\": 4999, \"to\": 5039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"L\\u00c3\\u00a9-on!\", \"from\": 5040, \"to\": 5047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"L\\u00c3\\u00a9-on!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Started up again.\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 10:33 p.m. he was introduced again to yet another eruption.\", \"from\": 5077, \"to\": 5139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand adjusted the back fin on the starting block, stripped off his coat and sweats, jumped once and then got on the blocks to do it all again.\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This race, he led from the start, with the only doubt being whether he could hold off the famously hard-closing Stubblety-Cook in the final lap.\", \"from\": 5288, \"to\": 5432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t just hold the Aussie off.\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He pulled away, sending the night to a deafening crescendo.\", \"from\": 5478, \"to\": 5537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon touching the wall, Marchand pulled himself up on the lane line and slammed his right hand down on the water\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094simultaneously tipping over backward as he did so.\", \"from\": 5538, \"to\": 5703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then he came up and slapped the water again, hoisted himself out of the pool and shoved two fists in the air.\", \"from\": 5704, \"to\": 5813, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was exhausted but elated by a shock-and-awe triumph.\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Bowman said the idea of attempting this double was more Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s than his\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094even as recently as a week ago.\", \"from\": 5871, \"to\": 5986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5871, \"end\": 5874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"score\": 0.9999862228881734, \"rank\": 1.377548726985259e-05, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\"}, {\"begin\": 5875, \"end\": 5881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But everything kept unfolding as hoped along the way to this night, so Bowman fully endorsed the decision.\", \"from\": 5987, \"to\": 6093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6058, \"end\": 6064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI obviously doubted [heading into the Olympics] a bit because everyone was telling me it was impossible,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Marchand said.\", \"from\": 6095, \"to\": 6220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6206, \"end\": 6214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBob told me after the400 meter individual medley: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098O.K., let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s do it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 That gave me confidence.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c  That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Bowman,Marchand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s coach and partner in dreaming big.\", \"from\": 6221, \"to\": 6393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6224, \"end\": 6227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"score\": 0.9999862228881734, \"rank\": 1.377548726985259e-05, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago, Marchand sent a cold-call email to Bowman asking if he could get a scholarship to swim for him at Arizona State.\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6446, \"end\": 6452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 6509, \"end\": 6522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\", \"score\": 0.9316018201508562, \"rank\": 0.07341997156043975, \"text\": \"Arizona State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bowman recognized the last name\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Xavier Marchand, L\\u00c3\\u00a9on\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s father, was an Olympic swimmer in the 1990s\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and the kid had solid times, so he took him onboard.\", \"from\": 6524, \"to\": 6683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6524, \"end\": 6530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 6558, \"end\": 6573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xavier_Marchand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xavier Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xavier_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xavier_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What Bowman quickly found out was that Marchand had the work ethic to match his natural ability.\", \"from\": 6685, \"to\": 6781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6690, \"end\": 6696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 6724, \"end\": 6732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999994188329, \"rank\": 5.486837676391794e-10, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And nobody is better at pushing, pulling and demanding excellence out of a talented swimmer than Bowman.\", \"from\": 6782, \"to\": 6886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6879, \"end\": 6885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He helped Michael Phelps aspire to make history.\", \"from\": 6888, \"to\": 6936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bowman coached him to eight victories in Beijing in 2008\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the literal gold standard in the sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and guided him to 28 total medals, 23 of them gold.\\u00c2  Marchand won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t ever reach those career numbers, unless France suddenly can win multiple relays at multiple Olympics.\", \"from\": 6937, \"to\": 7209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6937, \"end\": 6943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 6978, \"end\": 6985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.375560846158223e-12, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7148, \"end\": 7154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9380858284552133, \"rank\": 0.06565678020725985, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he found a way to make his own history with this double.\", \"from\": 7210, \"to\": 7270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I asked Bowman, who has played a key role in some of the most memorable achievements in swimming, whether this was the greatest single-day performance of them all.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s up there,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Bowman said.\", \"from\": 7271, \"to\": 7475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7282, \"end\": 7288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 7463, \"end\": 7469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s up there.\", \"from\": 7476, \"to\": 7495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a night he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll never forget.\", \"from\": 7496, \"to\": 7536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope he just remembers everything about it.\", \"from\": 7537, \"to\": 7582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cQuite honestly, this whole meet is about me fulfilling a promise I made to the kid three years ago.\", \"from\": 7584, \"to\": 7686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that I could come through and deliver.\", \"from\": 7687, \"to\": 7729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only was it a challenge for him, but it was a huge one for me.\", \"from\": 7730, \"to\": 7796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Being able to help him meet this moment is amazing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The next moment to meet is Thursday morning, in preliminaries of the 200 IM.\", \"from\": 7797, \"to\": 7929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time Marchand and Bowman left the arena just before midnight Wednesday, it was time to wipe off the face paint and put away the phone.\", \"from\": 7930, \"to\": 8071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7955, \"end\": 7961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.9999766550005147, \"rank\": 2.3345544840091698e-05, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bowman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d already flipped their minds forward to that task.\", \"from\": 8072, \"to\": 8130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest of us won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t get there nearly that fast.\", \"from\": 8132, \"to\": 8182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone who was present in La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena just witnessed the greatest night in swimming history, so forgive us if it takes a while to come down from that raucous high.\", \"from\": 8183, \"to\": 8354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 8356, \"to\": 8382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Pat Forde is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated who covers college football and college basketball as well as the Olympics and horse racing.\", \"from\": 8383, \"to\": 8591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8447, \"end\": 8456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pat Forde\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\"}, {\"begin\": 8480, \"end\": 8498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3451347450745126e-40, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He cohosts the College Football Enquirer podcast and is a football analyst on the Big Ten Network.\", \"from\": 8592, \"to\": 8690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8674, \"end\": 8689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Big Ten Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He previously worked for Yahoo Sports, ESPN and The (Louisville) Courier-Journal.\", \"from\": 8691, \"to\": 8772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8716, \"end\": 8728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"score\": 0.815096196264302, \"rank\": 0.22684904844294426, \"text\": \"Yahoo Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 8730, \"end\": 8734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5067256708891888e-24, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/